Sentencas: This paper presents the catalytic role of the gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) and its surface grain boundaries in enhancing the oxygen incorporation kinetics of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFC).
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Epitaxial and polycrystalline GDC thin films were grown by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) on the cathode side of 300 mu m-thick single crystalline (100) and 100 mu m-thick polycrystalline YSZ substrates, respectively.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Fuel cell current-voltage behavior and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements were carried out in the temperature range of 350 degrees C-450 degrees C on both types of cells.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Results of dc and ac measurements confirm that cathodic resistances of cells with epitaxial GDC layer are lower than that for the YSZ-only control cell.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This is attributed to the higher surface exchange coefficient for GDC than YSZ.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the role of grain boundary density at the cathode side external surface was investigated on surface-engineered electrode-membrane assemblies (MEA) having different GDC surface grain sizes.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: MEAs having smaller surface grain size show better cell performance and correspondingly lower electrode interfacial resistance.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical measurements suggest that GDC grain boundaries at the cathode side contribute to enhance oxygen surface kinetics.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results provide an opportunity and a microstructure design pathway to improve performance of LT-SOFCs by surface engineering with nano-granular, catalytically superior thin GDC cathodic interlayers.
Titulo: Epitaxial and Polycrystalline Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Cathode Interlayers for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
